A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Commercial Law – Voice and Visual Likeness – Digital Replication Rights
3 (Nurture Originals, Foster Art, and Keep Entertainment Safe Act – NO FAKES
4 Act)
5 FOR the purpose of establishing that each individual and a certain right holder have the
6 right to authorize the use of the voice or visual likeness of the individual in a digital
7 replica; providing that the right does not expire on the death of the individual and is
8 transferable or licensable in a certain manner; providing that the right terminates
9 after a certain period of time; requiring an online service to designate an agent to
10 receive a certain notification alleging a violation of this Act; requiring the Secretary
11 of State to maintain and make available certain information that the Secretary of
12 State receives from certain parties; providing that a person shall be civilly liable for
13 engaging in certain conduct in violation of this Act; providing that a person may not
14 be held civilly liable under certain circumstances; providing that an online service
15 may restore removed material under certain circumstances; and generally relating
16 to a right to the use of an individual’s voice or visual likeness in a digital replica.
17 BY adding to
18 Article – Commercial Law
19 Section 11–1701 through 11–1707 to be under the new subtitle “Subtitle 17. Rights
20 in Digital Replicas”
21 Annotated Code of Maryland
22 (2013 Replacement Volume and 2024 Supplement)
23 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
24 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
